00:27:39.200 --> 00:27:40.540
sir, because it lets me
shill like nobody's business.

00:27:40.540 --> 00:27:43.840
So for those who don't
know, I also do kids' books.

00:27:43.840 --> 00:27:47.040
When my sons and daughter
were born, I was just tired

00:27:47.040 --> 00:27:49.190
of them looking at reality
TV show stars and people

00:27:49.190 --> 00:27:51.090
who were famous for
being famous.

00:27:51.090 --> 00:27:53.590
And I said, you know what,
I have so many better heroes

00:27:53.590 --> 00:27:54.950
that we can give them.

00:27:54.950 --> 00:27:57.080
And we started with
I am Amelia Earhart

00:27:57.080 --> 00:27:58.450
and I am Abraham Lincoln.

00:27:58.450 --> 00:28:01.110
We did I am Rosa Parks, Albert
Einstein, Jackie Robinson.

00:28:01.110 --> 00:28:02.850
Because my son loves sports.

00:28:02.850 --> 00:28:05.590
And I was like, don't look
at this athlete, you know,

00:28:05.590 --> 00:28:07.350
who all that person does
is score a lot of points.

00:28:07.350 --> 00:28:10.210
It doesn't change
the world in any way.

00:28:10.210 --> 00:28:11.510
Meet Jackie Robinson.

00:28:11.510 --> 00:28:12.860
This is how you change
the world.

00:28:12.860 --> 00:28:15.090
This is what a leader
looks like.

00:28:15.090 --> 00:28:16.720
We did George Washington.

00:28:16.720 --> 00:28:19.110
We did Lucille Ball -- I did for
my daughter because I wanted her

00:28:19.110 --> 00:28:21.400
to have a female entertainment
hero who wasn't just famous

00:28:21.400 --> 00:28:23.300
for being thin and pretty.

00:28:23.300 --> 00:28:26.260
That Lucille Ball stood for
the idea that it's not just OK

00:28:26.260 --> 00:28:30.080
to be different, it's
spectacular to be different.

00:28:30.080 --> 00:28:32.900
The only thing that connects
us in this room completely

00:28:32.900 --> 00:28:36.410
that is true for all of us
is we are all different.

00:28:36.410 --> 00:28:38.610
It is something that
we just frown on today,

00:28:38.610 --> 00:28:40.390
but it is the most
celebrated thing

00:28:40.390 --> 00:28:43.510
that we should hold
up is our difference.

00:28:43.510 --> 00:28:45.670
And I love that I am
Lucille Ball stood for that.

00:28:45.670 --> 00:28:49.030
We did Helen Keller,
I am Dr. King.

00:28:49.030 --> 00:28:50.570
We did I am Jane Goodall,
also for my daughter

00:28:50.570 --> 00:28:51.970
because she loves our dog.

00:28:51.970 --> 00:28:54.520
And I wanted to show her what
your love of something can do.

00:28:54.520 --> 00:28:56.900
Jane Goodall used
her love of animals

00:28:56.900 --> 00:28:59.310
to just have breakthroughs
in science and make us look

00:28:59.310 --> 00:29:02.520
and study animals in a way
that has changed since.

00:29:02.520 --> 00:29:05.890
And we did for my youngest
son, who's our creative one,

00:29:05.890 --> 00:29:08.000
I did I am Jim Henson.

00:29:08.000 --> 00:29:09.300
Because I can tell you

00:29:09.300 --> 00:29:11.720
when I was five years old
watching Sesame Street

00:29:11.720 --> 00:29:14.920
and Mr. Rogers that
they taught me

00:29:14.920 --> 00:29:16.370
that you could use
your creativity

00:29:16.370 --> 00:29:18.530
to put good into this world.

00:29:18.530 --> 00:29:20.010
And when we did I am Jim Henson,

00:29:20.010 --> 00:29:23.440
that's all I hope I'm doing here
today is using my creativity

00:29:23.440 --> 00:29:25.380
to try and put good
into this world.

00:29:25.380 --> 00:29:27.170
And I love that we
get to do that book,

00:29:27.170 --> 00:29:30.140
got to work with Jim Henson's
family to put that book out.

00:29:30.140 --> 00:29:32.500
And we've done Harriet
Tubman, we've done Gandhi --

00:29:32.500 --> 00:29:35.050
which again, we need
right now, right?

00:29:35.050 --> 00:29:36.900
Just think about how much
were slaughtering each other

00:29:36.900 --> 00:29:38.200
every day.

00:29:38.200 --> 00:29:39.730
Hate, hate hating each other.

00:29:39.730 --> 00:29:42.440
Whatever your side is,
you hate the other.

00:29:42.440 --> 00:29:44.280
And we need to actually
find peace.

00:29:44.280 --> 00:29:46.360
We need to actually
be able to calm down

00:29:46.360 --> 00:29:47.860
and communicate in
a peaceful way.

00:29:47.860 --> 00:29:50.970
That's what inspired Dr.
King, and there's a reason.

00:29:50.970 --> 00:29:53.800
And it actually leads
me to the two newest --

00:29:53.800 --> 00:29:56.780
